IRPC, Siam Commercial Bank, True Corp.: Thailand Equity Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-04-07T02:16:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/irpc-siam-commercial-bank-true-corp-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The SET Index fell 2.53, or 0.2 percent, to 1,076.13.  IRPC Pcl (IRPC)  : The Thai petrochemical maker named
Prasert Bunsumpun, president of parent PTT Pcl, as chairman of
the board, the company said in a regulatory filing. IRPC rose
2.5 percent to 6.25 baht.  Siam Commercial Bank Pcl (SCB)  : The lender will probably
increase its loan growth target for the full year as economic
growth in Thailand boosts demand for credit, Executive Chairman
Vichit Suraphongchai said. Siam Commercial was unchanged at 115
baht.  True Corp. (TRUE TB): Investors who buy the shares today
will not be entitled to the company’s rights offer. True, the
operator of Thailand’s third-largest mobile phone network, plans
to raise 13 billion baht ($431 million) by selling 6.73 billion
new shares to existing shareholders, the company said on March
28. True dropped 1.6 percent to 4.23 baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  